    "body": "\r\nfor dpskv4, the k_norm is used nowhere, and can be deleted.\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\nk_norm is used in deepseek v3.2 not in deepseek v4, it's defined in __init__ but never called in forward(), this won't raise an error, because vllm now only enable strict check for non-quantized models,\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/blob/ff712f6447093d07747c88680b9d006b119f5890/vllm/model_executor/model_loader/default_loader.py#L401-L412\r\n\r\nI converted fp8 weight to bfloat16, and it raises error.\r\n\r\n```\r\nValueError: Following weights were not initialized from checkpoint: {'model.layers.14.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.38.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.14.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.12.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.36.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.10.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.20.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.10.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.24.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.6.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.16.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.6.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.28.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.2.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.22.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.34.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.4.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.22.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.38.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.26.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.34.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.4.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.8.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.18.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.24.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.30.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.18.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.12.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.42.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.40.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.28.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.16.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.26.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.2.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.36.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.42.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.40.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.20.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.8.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.32.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias', 'model.layers.32.attn.indexer.k_norm.weight', 'model.layers.30.attn.indexer.k_norm.bias'}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n## Test Result\r\n\r\n---\r\n<details>\r\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\r\n\r\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\r\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\r\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\r\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\r\n</details>\r\n\r\ncc @WoosukKwon",
